-- Chinese Oil Firms Start Investing in Xinjiang Energy, Business Today Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-28T06:39:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/chinese-oil-firms-start-investing-in-xinjiang-energy-business-today-says.html

          
          
             China National Petroleum Corp.,
China Petrochemical Corp. and China National Offshore Oil Corp.
have begun first-stage investment in an energy development plan
in the northwest Xinjiang region of China, Beijing Business
Today reported, citing Xu Fengxian, a researcher at the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences.  
 The energy plan will likely be submitted to the State
Council by the end of the year, the report said, without citing
anyone.  
